title: Australia's High Commissioner visits Jersey
text:
Dozens of New Zealand and Australian ex-pats are expected to gather at Jersey's cenotaph today for a commemoration to remember lives lost in the First World War.
It is taking place at 4pm. The Australian High Commissioner is visiting the island today.
15 Jersey men fought and lost their lives in Gallipoli fighting for the Australian Armed Forces. Jersey also became home to Australian soldiers at the end of the First World War.
More than 500 Australian and New Zealand born nationals were recorded as living in Jersey in the last census.
Last updated Mon 19 Oct 2015 Politics Jersey
